10 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
11 An Act relating to the 2030 Decennial Census;
creating the U.S. Decennial Census Revolving Fund;
12 establishing the fund at Commerce; deeming funds
appropriated; providing expenditure and budgeting
13 requirements and limitations; and providing an
effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5095 of Title 74, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
21 for the Oklahoma Department of Commerce to be designated the "U.S.
22 Decennial Census Revolving Fund". The fund shall be a continuing
23 fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of
24 all monies received by the Oklahoma Department of Commerce as
HB3622 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 dire cted by law. All monies accruing to the credit of said fund are
2 hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Oklahoma
3 Department of Commerce for the purpose of preparing for any upcoming
4 federal decennial census, including the upgrade of required
5 technology. Expenditures from said fund shall be made upon warrants
6 issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by
7 law with the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
8 Services for approval and payment.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
10
11 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON APPROPRIATIONS AND BUDGET, dated
02/25/2026 - DO PASS, As Amended and Coauthored.
